uk.ac.aber.group14.viewer

Class WalkCreatorActivity

  • java.lang.Object
    • Activity
      • uk.ac.aber.group14.viewer.WalkCreatorActivity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IUploadFinishNotify

    public class WalkCreatorActivity
extends Activity
implements IUploadFinishNotify
    This activity is used to actually record the walks. It dislays the user's latitude and longitude, and allows the user cancel or upload the walk, as well as adding a point of interest. If the user does not have any GPS coordinates or points of interest then they cannot upload, and a dialog will tell them this. When the user adds a location the LocationActivity is launched. When the user uploads the walk, the WalkUploader AsyncTask is executed and a progress dialog shows on their screen until it is complete.

      • onSaveRoute

        public void onSaveRoute(View view)
        This method is called by the "Upload Walk" button. It determines if the walk can be uploaded (at least 1 POI, 1 GPS Location) and then creates a new WalkUploader AsyncTask. This is then provided with our alertDialog and progressDailog and executed. If the user cannot upload a walk then they are told so with an alert dialog.

      • onDismiss

        public void onDismiss(DialogInterface dialog)
        We override this to tell when an alert dialog has been dismissed. If isFinished is true then we call "finish()" and exit. if isFinished is false then we set "isUploading" to false (this is because if we were given an alert dialog then we are not currently uploading as we have just informed the user that either they cannot upload, the upload worked, or the upload failed.
        See Also:
        android.content.DialogInterface.OnDismissListener#onDismiss(android.content.DialogInterface)
